cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with game theory and information theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of the method of types and the idea of random hashing also suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of computational aspects of entropy-payoff trade-off curve suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
